{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, Section 6 provides the conclusion of the article, summarizing the key points we discovered while working on our review paper.",
    "Recently, we require robots that can move around and work well in places they have never been before.",
    "In this regard, simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) emerges as a fundamental approach for these robots.",
    "The primary goal of SLAM is to autonomously explore and navigate unknown environments by simultaneously creating a map and determining their own position (Durrant-Whyte, 2012; Mohamed et al., 2008).",
    "Furthermore, it provides real-time capabilities, allowing robots to make decisions on-the-fly without relying on pre-existing maps."
  ]
}